Title: A Bayesian approach to model the dynamics of gene regulatory networks,
Abstract: We propose a Bayesian approach to model the dynamics of gene regulatory networks (GRNs) using a system of ordinary differential equations (ODEs). The proposed method allows for the incorporation of prior knowledge about the network structure and parameter values, and provides a framework for model selection and uncertainty quantification. We demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method on a simple synthetic network and a real biological network, the Escherichia coli lactose metabolism network.

Abstract: In this study, we present a machine learning model for predicting protein-ligand binding affinity. We demonstrate the effectiveness of our model by comparing its predictions to experimental data and showing that it outperforms existing methods in terms of accuracy and generalization.

Title: A Bayesian approach to modeling gene regulatory networks,
Abstract: We propose a Bayesian framework for modeling gene regulatory networks. The model is based on a set of differential equations that describe the dynamics of gene expression levels over time. We use Bayesian inference to estimate the parameters of the model from experimental data, and we show that our approach can accurately predict the behavior of gene regulatory networks in response to perturbations.
